\sum_{k=0}^{n}\frac{1}{(k+1)(k+2)}\binom{n}{k}
(1+x)^n=\sum {{n}\choose{k}} x^k
=\sum_{k=0}^{n}\frac{k!}{k!(k+1)(k+2)}\binom{n}{k} =\sum_{k=0}^{n}\frac{k!}{(k+2)!}\cdot\frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!} \\=\sum_{k=0}^{n}\frac{n!}{(k+2)!(n-k)!} \\=\frac{1}{(n+1)(n+2)}\sum_{k=0}^{n}\frac{(n+2)!}{(k+2)!(n-k)!} \\=\frac{1}{(n+1)(n+2)}\sum_{k=0}^{n}\binom{n+2}{k+2}
(1 + x)^n = \sum_{k=0} ^n \binom{n}{k} x^k
x
 \frac{(1+x)^{n+1}}{n+1} = \int (1 + x)^n \, \mathrm{d}x  = \int \sum_{k=0} ^n \binom{n}{k} x^k \, \mathrm{d}x = \sum_{k=0} ^n \binom{n}{k} \int x^k \, \mathrm{d}x = \sum_{k=0} ^n \binom{n}{k} \frac{x^{k+1}}{k+1} . 
(1+x)^n=\sum {{n}\choose{k}} x^k
